			<abstract>
				<p>Testimony of Hanuš Gibian, which became a part of the “documentation campaign” in Prague. Gibian was imprisoned together with his wife and son in the Nováky labor camp in Slovakia. During the Slovak National Uprising in the fall of 1944, they escaped from the camp and hid in the
					mountains near Banská Bystrica. In November 1944, they were caught by German troops. Gibian describes the execution of more than forty Jews. He was shot and survived only due to the fact that he pretended to be dead.</p>
			</abstract>
